  {"title":"General — Letters of Support Template Guidance","funder_name":"General","funder_type":"general","program_name":"General Grants","cfda_number":None,"section_key":"attachments","section_title":"Letters of Support / Partnership Letters","org_types":["nonprofit","municipal"],"program_types":["general"],"tags":["general","letters_of_support","partnerships","MOU"],"win_count":13,"use_count":39,"typical_word_limit":300,"content_md":"**Effective letters of support include:**\n\n1. *Who is writing:* Name, title, organization, and their relationship to the applicant\n2. *What they know:* Specific evidence they have observed the applicant's work and competence\n3. *What they commit to:* Specific, concrete commitments (not just general support) — referrals, data sharing, co-location, in-kind resources, collaborative activities\n4. *Why this matters:* Their stake in the problem and why this project is the right solution\n\n**Red flags reviewers notice:**\n- Generic letters with no specific project reference\n- Letters that only say 'we support this organization' with no specific commitments\n- Letters from organizations with no evident connection to the target population\n- Letters that are clearly templates with fill-in-the-blank names\n\n**Sample language for commitment paragraph:**\n'[Partner Organization] commits to: (1) referring [X] eligible clients/month to [Program]; (2) providing co-located space at [Address] for [X] days/week at no cost; (3) sharing de-identified outcome data for program evaluation purposes; and (4) participating in [X] joint training events per year.'"},

